&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Seller Systems team owns an expansive mix of platform and product problems. We are looking for people with a strong background or interest in working across these domains to build successful platforms and systems. You’re comfortable dealing with many moving pieces, and you work effectively across teams and functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be focused on defining and delivering capabilities and experiences that span product, backroom accounting, end-user reporting and go-to-market unlocking product velocity and monetization in a compliant and scalable manner for Stripe. As fintech continues to transform offline and digital businesses, your work will enable Stripe’s sellers and go-to-market teams to operate efficiently and support Stripe’s expanding commercial portfolio and full suite of financial products. Your work will accelerate the sold funnel by improving the seller experience and core underlying capabilities. It’s a chance to have a huge impact on increasing the GDP of the Internet!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On a day to day basis you will spend your time split between meetings with internal customers (GTM, Accounting, Product Teams), external customers and discussions with your engineering, design, analytics, and operations counterparts. You will identify the most important problems to solve, develop product solutions and work with engineering and design to scope the work. You will articulate the product vision, develop annual and quarterly plans, and collaborate with other functions to deliver these solutions to our users and make them successful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong product sense: ability to understand user needs in-depth and build delightful product experiences to solve them and make our users successful&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deeply understand the users and downstream consumers of this data touching multiple business domains, by working with Stripe’s users, and with Stripe’s technical and business teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with engineering leaders to design ingestion, enrichment, storage and serving interfaces to meet these user needs. You’ll to synthesize and champion the various users’ and stakeholders’ to ensure we create surprisingly great experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical skills e.g., ability to gain an in-depth understanding of software systems, make meaningful contributions to high-stakes discussions on API design, data modeling and software architecture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong customer empathy across different segments and personas: from internal customers in GTM, accounting, data science and engineering to disparate end-user segments such as startups and large enterprises.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills: ability to synthesize complex discussions, write succinctly and present to senior stakeholders both within and outside Stripe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive product strategy and roadmap for part of this critical infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a leader, do-er and change agent in helping us execute effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience as a Product Manager in technology companies. Experience managing and mentoring Product Managers is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding and experience with Go-to-Market systems and processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building platform infrastructure that serves and balances the needs of multiple users and stakeholders. You’re excited by thinking through the right balance between flexibility and consistency, and comfortable communicating prioritization among competing user needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously evolving technical systems to keep up with growth and evolving needs of the business transforming legacy systems into their next generation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work cross functionally and speak multiple ‘languages’: you’re equally credible as a thought partner for Go-to-Market, Engineering, Finance or Legal leaders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Most importantly, we’re looking for great product managers who deeply understand their users, turn that into great plans, and make those plans happen. Even if you don’t have all the experience above we’d encourage you to apply if this role excites you&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience managing technical software products from infancy to scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can internalize an entire cross-functional business and lead a comprehensive product vision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience designing and building a multi-product platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re a creative product thinker who loves collaborating across the company with engineering, analytics, marketing, design and sales to experiment and build superior products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have strong written and verbal communication skills with a talent for precise articulations of customer problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re motivated by the chance to improve the lives of your users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re scrappy, you do what it takes to get it done&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Infrastructure and Data Experiences Product Team (“IDX” for short) is responsible for ensuring that Stripe’s major engineering systems are meeting the needs of our customers - both internal teams and external users. We partner closely with Stripe’s CTO, Engineering leads and Product leads across Stripe to define technology vision, product capabilities, and roadmaps, while delivering reliable experiences for our customers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Product Manager on the team, you&#39;ll work with Stripe tech leaders to:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grow the business through delightful user experiences and reliable infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Streamline decision making and business operations through state of the art systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver the best experience for developers in the industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe’s infrastructure is composed of high availability distributed systems that power Stripe products. We’re looking for a product manager who loves developers and works with them daily to understand their needs, has a knack for building beautiful product experiences with ergonomic user journeys, isn’t afraid of understanding large technical systems, and prioritizes users and business impact. The problems you will be working on are critical to unlock the next phase of growth at Stripe, ranging from unlocking international markets through local infrastructure to powering enterprise-grade experiences.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the engineering teams, including Core Infra, Developer Infra, Data Platform, and Service Platform, to ship functionality that delights users, has the right balance of impact vs engineering cost, and makes a measurable impact on the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish system and design principles for how we build, buy, and operate Seller Systems — ensuring we select the right long-term solutions, not short-term patches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide architecture and investment decisions, weighing trade-offs between build vs. buy, modernization vs. extension, and platform vs. point solution to maintain a cohesive, sustainable ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interact with external users and propose critical infrastructure abstractions that best serve them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate product ideas and prototypes with early adopters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define key success metrics for developer products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on infrastructure, API, data models/pipelines roadmaps&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on internal AI agents for specific functions such as Recruiting, Legal etc. to aid productivity and great customer experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal Product Manager will be relentlessly user-focused, highly analytical, comfortable in ambiguity, have strong technical skills, and the desire to create something new.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;7+ years of progressive experience&lt;/strong&gt; in Product Management, ideally within an enterprise or B2B setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Demonstrated success&lt;/strong&gt; in defining, launching, and scaling complex products from ideation to general availability in an enterprise environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proven ability to manage diverse stakeholders&lt;/strong&gt; (Engineering, Design, Sales, Marketing, Executive Leadership) and drive cross-functional alignment on product vision and prioritization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exceptional ability to map, analyze, and refine Customer User Journeys (CUJs)&lt;/strong&gt; to identify high-value pain points and opportunities for AI solution deployment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Highly data-driven approach&lt;/strong&gt; to prioritization and decision-making, including the ability to define key performance indicators (KPIs), create product impact dashboards, and synthesize data into actionable product requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A track record of leveraging qualitative (customer interviews) and quantitative (product usage data)&lt;/strong&gt; insights to validate assumptions and drive product strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/strong&gt;, with the ability to articulate complex technical concepts and product strategies clearly to both technical and non-technical audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI &amp;amp; Technical Expertise&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hands-on experience&lt;/strong&gt; developing and launching AI/ML-powered products or features for internal or external customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Robust functional and technical understanding of Large Language Models (LLMs)&lt;/strong&gt; and common AI-based workflows (e.g., retrieval-augmented generation, fine-tuning, prompt engineering).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prior experience&lt;/strong&gt; working directly with LLMs or launching conversational AI agents into production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical background&lt;/strong&gt; (e.g., Computer Science degree or equivalent practical experience) that allows for deep engagement with engineering teams on technical trade-offs and architectural decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with cross-geo/timezone environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of solving high-impact, cross-system challenges and aligning senior stakeholders across Product, Engineering, and Core infrastructure organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Support Experience team develops and applies technology at all points of the user support journey to solve customer problems at scale, unlocking growth across Stripe’s product suite.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Product Manager on the Support Experience PM team, you’ll be responsible for defining the strategy for Consumer Support - solve problems for a fast growing segment at Stripe. You’ll need to tackle this space from multiple angles, from motivating product teams at Stripe to understand and improve product quality, to building systems that allow for repeatable problem solving by both users and our support team. You’ll need to create observability across inbound and outbound volume to find the high impact drivers of poor experiences; and build the flywheels that will leverage our internal and external systems to continuously improve how problems are resolved and products are built.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive significant increases in product quality across the company leveraging support data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the flywheels for improving support outcomes and enabling users to self-solve issues by creating scalable knowledge and workflow strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Product Managers for the Self-Serve and Agent Platforms to define and instrument user journeys across our products so we can understand how success differs by journey and where we should invest&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define the data strategy for delivering an effective and efficient support experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a platform that can be leveraged across the support journey to turbocharge users and support agents’ ability to solve problems directly and reliably&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal Product Manager will be relentlessly user-focused, comfortable in ambiguity, have strong technical skills, and the desire to create something new.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of relevant product management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Computer Science background or equivalent technical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical abilities and experience with metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An ability to craft a vision and strategy and drive the roadmap toward it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A deep empathy for users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Software engineering experience, a computer science or engineering degree, or similar technical experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe Terminal helps our users extend their online presence to the physical world. The Terminal team’s mission is to make it as easy for businesses to accept in-person payments as the Stripe API has done for online payments. With Terminal, businesses can unlock in-person payments use cases that are right for their business model—whether it’s creating a superb retail experience, extending their website to a pop-up store, or enabling a mobile point-of-sale at their next event.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an experienced product manager to lead and shape the future of the software platform that powers Stripe Terminal’s devices portfolio. Working closely with your engineering partners you will design, build and launch device software capabilities that delight users and differentiate Stripe’s solutions in the market. Working closely with our hardware experts you will build the multi-year strategy for how Stripe will continue to enhance the scalability, reliability, usability, and market differentiation of the software capabilities of our in-person commerce devices.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will work with a spectrum of users, from our largest platforms to small start ups as well as external technology partners to deeply understand user needs and market trends. You will obsess over stability, scalability, and expanding our product while delivering the best in person experiences in the world.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Set a motivating multi-year vision for device software in partnership with the Hardware team and then break it down into measurable, meaningful milestones for the Terminal OS Platform Team and the Firmware team. This includes creating buy-in, crafting roadmaps and OKRs, and navigating trade-offs.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with software and hardware engineers to deeply understand the technology that our devices rely on and how to build on that technology to support exponential growth and a world-class user experience. These experiences will include (but are not limited to) device boot up, device software updates (including AOSP, firmware and applications), device security, software and device performance, connectivity and devices accessories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional partners to research, document, and deeply understand what Terminal customers need to enable an excellent in person payments experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build empathy with our end users and the differentiation they aim to deliver for their merchants.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deeply research and understand the competitive landscape and translate that understanding into differentiating features for your product suite.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the Partnerships team to develop a compelling roadmap for how we can extend Terminal growth via third-party hardware partnerships and clearly communicate the business value of these partnerships in the context of our wider Terminal Hardware roadmap to gain alignment across Terminal and Stripe leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use metrics to inform your point of view and leverage analytics to measure success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define product requirements, provide clear guidance on prioritization, and support decisions related to development sequencing. You will also participate in sprint planning rituals to deliver against those requirements and the overall roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage your technical knowledge and experience to help your team make technical trade off decisions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re looking for someone who has:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of product management experience or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success and strong execution track record in building and sustaining scalable technology products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great interpersonal skills and strong verbal and written communication. You can collaborate and thrive in productive, healthy debate done with mutual respect and shared goals. You can make complex concepts accessible with clear communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of successful stakeholder management including executive communications, handling escalations, and advocating for ongoing investment in your product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working on products with developer interfaces (App deployment, APIs, SDKs); hardware or hardware-related product experience a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technically adept systems thinker, ideally with a Computer Science or equivalent degree or experience working as a software engineer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open to travel to Asia, including traveling at times to our Hong Kong or Taiwan locations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Experience in 1 - 2 of the following areas are nice to have:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mobile device management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Android operating system internals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hardware build and lifecycle management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Payments and/or eCommerce&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience successfully building and launching 0-1 products&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe Terminal helps our users extend their online presence to the physical world. The Terminal team’s mission is to make it as easy for businesses to accept in-person payments as the Stripe API has done for online payments. With Terminal, businesses can unlock in-person payments use cases that are right for their business model—whether it’s creating a superb retail experience, extending their website to a pop-up store, or enabling a mobile point-of-sale at their next event.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Terminal is one of the fastest growing products at Stripe and we are building a uniquely powerful unified commerce platform for global enterprises, offering a single integration to unlock in-person payments, fast and low cost cross-border money movement, AI powered optimizations and fraud protection, reporting and differentiated ways to pay. As the Terminal Unified Commerce PM, you will be responsible for building this end to end platform.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Stripe’s unified commerce platform for Enterprise users worldwide&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate at both a massive and nuanced scale, identifying holistic investments for Stripe as well as specific needs for users. Represent Terminal and Stripe in external forums like&amp;nbsp; front of users: directly engaging in product discovery and roadmapping conversations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;S&lt;/em&gt;et a motivating multi-year vision and then break it down into measurable, meaningful milestones for the Terminal Enterprise team. This includes creating buy-in, crafting roadmaps and OKRs, and navigating trade-offs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with various teams&amp;nbsp; at Stripe like product partnerships, product marketing, partner marketing, product legal and vertical industry teams to collaborate on user and partner needs, industry events, and GTM motions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re looking for someone who has:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of product management experience or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working on B2B products, ideally with a track record of building for external users&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technically adept systems thinker, ideally with an engineering degree strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great interpersonal skills and strong verbal and written communication. You can make complex concepts accessible with clear communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to haves:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success and strong execution track record in building payment products&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Alliances &amp;amp; Channels (A&amp;amp;C) team is responsible for building a vibrant ecosystem of partners that accelerates Stripe’s mission. Within A&amp;amp;C, the Programs team drives partner success and ecosystem growth at scale through programs, incentives, enablement, and operational rigor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be the AMER analytics and execution engine for A&amp;amp;C Programs—turning partner motions (sales plays, SDR workflows, incentives) into measurable, repeatable operating systems. You will ship dashboards and program mechanics that make partner signals actionable for sellers and make program performance visible to leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is intentionally data-forward. It’s for someone who can independently go from ambiguous problem → metric definitions/data model → dashboard → operating cadence, and raise the quality bar in the process without needing a big team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain AMER dashboards and recurring reporting for partner program health and outcomes (adoption, partner-sourced inputs, play performance, incentives throughput)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently define metrics, data models, and documentation (definitions + user guides) so reporting is trusted and reusable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop seller-facing, read-only reporting experiences that make partner signals actionable (e.g., “my patch” views and account drilldowns with signal type/recency and the right Stripe contact)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with GTM Ops and data owners to improve data availability and correctness; identify gaps and drive pragmatic fixes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the A&amp;amp;C Programs operating interface with the sales development representatives that support partners including developing intake standards, routing rules, play briefs, QA loop, and weekly/monthly performance readouts tied to SLAs and pipeline outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operationalize and track the effectiveness of partner-ready sales plays end-to-end (inputs, workflows, scorecards, iteration loop) and drive a consistent cadence to monitor and improve execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve incentives/funding request readiness and cycle time via templates, completeness checks, and tracking—so incentives owners can focus on approvals/contracting while execution stays unblocked&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify at-risk program/analytics work and step in to unblock delivery when timelines or data quality are at risk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Who you are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in analytics, operations, program management, revenue operations, or a similar role in a GTM environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on analytics skill, including strong comfort with Salesforce and SQL (or equivalent) and demonstrated experience building dashboards that are used by operators and sellers (not just one-off analysis)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort working across imperfect data sources and improving definitions and data hygiene over time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience running cross-functional operating cadences (standing up workflows, aligning stakeholders, tracking actions, delivering outcomes)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear written communication skills; ability to write concise operating notes, metric definitions, templates, and status updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Familiarity with partner ecosystems (SIs, ISVs, platforms) and co-sell/co-deliver motions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Global Partner Engineering and Operations (PE&amp;amp;O) team is a vital part of Stripe’s Global Partnerships organization, playing a key role in our overall success. We manage the technical and operational dimensions of new and existing strategic product partnerships and programs. Positioned at the nexus of product development, engineering, and partnerships, we facilitate seamless collaboration essential for supporting Stripe’s rapid growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our team is a diverse mix of technical and business professionals dedicated to executing operations with financial ecosystem partners. We ensure efficient technical onboarding and implementation, while also overseeing ongoing KTLO (Keep-The-Lights-On) activities and achieving strict quality and performance benchmarks. Additionally, the PE&amp;amp;O team initiates partner-agnostic programs and solutions to tackle broad ecosystem challenges, developing tools that enhance operational efficiency and scalability.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In This Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team is establishing a new function to oversee Card Network Compliance. In this position, you will be responsible for developing programs and processes to address Stripe’s card network changes and their implications for both Stripe and its users. This role is crucial for ensuring we stay informed about ongoing card network announcements, enhancing our strategic position, and driving operational efficiency in response to changes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to contribute significantly to building a function from the ground up and to help formulate strategies that align with the best interests of Stripe and its users!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Implement Release Management Process: &lt;/strong&gt;Establish a release management process for Stripe in accordance with Card Network mandates, advising all cross-functional partners on the impacts, changes, and timelines associated with network updates. Conduct comprehensive analyses of how these mandates affect existing processes and services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Review Card Network Releases: &lt;/strong&gt;Review, analyze, and assess biannual card network releases to identify key initiatives that will significantly impact Stripe’s business. Collaborate cross-functionally with various teams to ensure proper visibility and prioritization of these initiatives. Facilitate communication between engineering teams and the card networks&#39; Technical Partner Managers (TPaMs) to streamline clarifications and negotiations regarding complex mandates and programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monitor Compliance: &lt;/strong&gt;Establish a framework and process for monitoring compliance with card network requirements and internal policies. Ensure regular audits and assessments are conducted to identify gaps and drive continuous improvement strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Develop Metrics and Dashboards: &lt;/strong&gt;Create and implement comprehensive metrics and JIRA dashboards to effectively monitor, review, and analyze mandates for each release cycle. Regularly update and refine the dashboards to reflect current business priorities and challenges, enabling teams to make informed decisions and proactively address potential issues related to card network mandates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage Mandate Intake Process: &lt;/strong&gt;Oversee the network mandate intake process, ensuring timely review, assessment, and prioritization of mandates. Lead the proactive management of waiver requests, liaising between compliance and operational teams for resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engage with External Partners: &lt;/strong&gt;Actively engage with external network partners by participating in councils, forums, and regular strategic meetings. Establish and nurture relationships that facilitate mutual understanding of goals and objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advocate for Stripe: &lt;/strong&gt;Serve as a dedicated advocate for Stripe within the card network ecosystem, ensuring that the unique perspectives, challenges, and opportunities faced by Stripe are considered by network stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in the payments industry, with significant expertise in working with card networks and understanding card network rules and compliance activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth understanding of acquiring platforms and systems, and their interactions with card network products and processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in navigating and using JIRA for project management and tracking. Familiarity with card network portals for managing and monitoring compliance activities. Comfortable utilizing Google Workspace tools (such as Sheets, Docs, and Slides) for collaboration and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of effectively collaborating with product and engineering teams to develop new processes and strategies in partnership with them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong program and project management abilities, with the capacity to engage and influence stakeholders outside of direct control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills to effectively engage with both internal and external partners and drive change.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to thrive with minimal guidance, navigating uncertainty and ambiguity while shaping a new program and function at Stripe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic thinker adept at identifying cross-functional issues, providing innovative solutions, and communicating the implications of these solutions across existing processes, systems, and teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience at a payment service provider (PSP), card network, or high-growth technology company&amp;nbsp; is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in a relevant field (e.g., Finance, Technology) is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Global Partner Engineering and Operations (PE&amp;amp;O) team is a vital part of Stripe’s Global Partnerships organization, playing a key role in our overall success. We manage the technical and operational dimensions of new and existing strategic product partnerships and programs. Positioned at the nexus of product development, engineering, and partnerships, we facilitate seamless collaboration essential for supporting Stripe’s rapid growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mission: We drive product-partnerships to create non-linear growth for our users and Stripe by developing relationships with partners that enable Stripe to create, enhance, drive adoption of, and monetize world-class products and a supporting ecosystem.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a skilled and motivated Operations Program Manager to join our Global Partner Engineering &amp;amp; Operations (PE&amp;amp;O) team at Stripe. This role will focus on driving excellent partner programs – managing initiatives that service a broad set of partners and their diverse requirements. As we continue to scale our operations, we are looking for an innovative Program Manager to join our team and help strengthen our relationships with payment institutions. This role requires a strong understanding of money movement, storage solutions, and the latest financial technologies. A strong background in program management, excellent organizational abilities, and a commitment to driving partner success are essential for this role. The ideal candidate will possess a unique combination of analytical skills, operational excellence, and collaborative problem-solving abilities.&amp;nbsp;The ideal candidate will be responsible for:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Implementing&lt;/strong&gt; best practices to improve partnership performance and drive strategic initiatives.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Driving &lt;/strong&gt;multiple projects that enhance partner integrations and operational efficiency, with a specific focus on driving the maturity and sophistication of programs over time.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborating&lt;/strong&gt; with cross-functional teams (engineering, operations, regulatory) to align on goals and deliver outcomes that meet partner needs and organizational objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Identify&lt;/strong&gt; trends and opportunities for enhancing money movement efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Program Accountability:&lt;/strong&gt; Take ownership of the program portfolio, ensuring alignment with strategic goals and objectives. Monitor and measure program performance against defined success criteria, resulting in actionable insights and continuous improvements..&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner Stakeholder Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop, manage, and execute end-to-end project plans to improve partner implementations and enhancements, communicating closely with some of Stripe’s key financial partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Coordination:&lt;/strong&gt; Facilitate alignment, coordination, and execution between internal teams (Engineering, Product, Partner Development, etc.) and external partners on critical operational activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Who you are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of program management experience, particularly with external partnerships and technical project management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with a focus on identifying opportunities for improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven proficiency in driving the maturity and sophistication of programs, including process efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in project management methodologies (e.g., Agile, Waterfall) and tools (e.g. JIRA).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills with experience developing quantitative frameworks and reporting tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong design and visualization skills for regular presentations, updates, data reports, and communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Risk Operations Enablement team sits within the Risk Operations org and is responsible for partnering across Risk teams. Our mission is to enable users to seamlessly meet evolving compliance standards in a complex regulatory environment. More specifically, our team focuses on Program management, User Insights, and Operational Efficiency. As an enablement function, we worked with many stakeholders including Operations, Product, Eng, GTM, and others. If you’re the type of person who enjoys working on high impact projects on a global scale, running programs from end to end, and advocating for users – you’ll love this role. Note: We do not require prior experience in Risk or Compliance to be considered for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you thrive on owning an expansive and complex topic area, teasing out the highest-impact work to tackle, rallying cross-functional support, and executing against multiple workstreams in parallel to hit your objectives, we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead complex global programs, from initial scoping to design and execution and work on high-impact strategic initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create structured approaches to user feedback and insights to improve our programs and user experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and launch projects that lead to step-change improvements in our operational processes and business outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with our cross-functional stakeholders to scope and execute large projects to create operational efficiencies that improve top-line metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a subject matter expert for working teams and build relationships with progressively more senior stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embody our Operating Principles and foster Stripe’s values and culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a strategic operator and powerful storyteller. You have significant experience writing 1-pagers, developing slide decks, and using data visualization tools – and your work serves as an inspiration to others. There’s no problem too large or small to solve; you pride yourself on being a problem solver.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in program management, strategy &amp;amp; operations, or go-to-market strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter; works independently and autonomously to drive outcomes for projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bias towards action and high accountability for outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong project and program leadership, ability to articulate strategy and project plans, and develop a clear point of view&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills; ability to present with confidence to senior stakeholders in a succinct, clear way&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong data analysis skills - can confidently analyze spreadsheets, navigate large datasets, and use data to tell stories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High willingness to learn and receive feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years in consulting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MBA preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience partnering with Product and Eng teams preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Stripe’s user base and global footprint grows dramatically, we have distinctly unique support problems resulting from both our type of scale and the type of businesses we partner with. The Stripe Delivery Center (SDC) strategy will provide operational leverage and expand Stripe’s portfolio of operational capabilities to support the scaled needs for external users and internal Stripe teams. Our support experience leverages deep understanding of our products, the financial industry and money movement, and our customers’ products and users, and requires us to invest significant resources into building this experience ourselves with talented teams of Stripes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for dynamic and entrepreneurial leaders who will define our strategy to scale our Core Payments team, help define and improve operational workflows, and maintain a best in class Operations program. If you like hard problems, are analytical, comfortable operating in ambiguity and finding creative solutions, we want to hear from you!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive operational excellence and support global expansion, global growth, and product teams by enhancing processes through effective stakeholder management, ensuring alignment and seamless execution across regions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee product launches by managing the horizontal product launch process, monitoring and reporting on progress with biweekly status updates to Senior leadership, while maintaining transparent documentation in Compass (Stripe Internal tool).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate cross-functional collaboration by identifying and documenting responsibilities of cross-functional teams for product launches, proactively communicating blockers, and providing transparent status updates to all involved teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define, enhance and improve operating rhythms to facilitate efficient collaboration across teams, managing operational cadences for planning cycles, business reviews, and tracking Stripe Objectives and Key Results (SOKRs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with stakeholders to prioritize initiatives and manage resource allocation, while facilitating the annual planning process by consolidating feedback and providing insights for leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement metrics to identify and eliminate inefficiencies (Muda) and standardize emerging processes with documented frameworks, partnering with Product, Engineering, Go-to-Market, Partnerships, and Legal teams to enhance operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Over 9 years of total working experience with 4-5 years in program management, consulting, or similar roles within high-growth tech companies, especially in payments or fintech, with a strong focus on managing strategic product initiatives from conception to implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record in process and project management, including creating operational processes, leading product roadmap reviews, and designing scalable systems in fast-paced environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled at scheduling, prioritizing tasks, and meeting deadlines to ensure timely delivery of products and features.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable in high-ambiguity situations, executing complex projects while fostering collaboration across diverse teams and functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong capabilities in stakeholder engagement, maintaining high-level planning and ongoing communication to align project goals with operations seamlessly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in presenting ideas, product updates, and roadmaps clearly and persuasively to various stakeholders, including executives, ensuring alignment and understanding of project objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with road map management tools planning frameworks and know-how to apply them to manage projects effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to understand the company&#39;s strategic goals and align the product roadmap accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled in helping stakeholders prioritize product features and initiatives based on business value, customer need, and resource availability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A deep understanding of global markets, and the ability to contextualize decisions and processes to accommodate regional nuances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in implementing process improvements and change management strategies to scale operations effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Third Party Risk Management team is accountable for defining, maintaining, and overseeing the third party risk framework, policy, and inventory in accordance with management expectations and best practices. We are focused on assessing and managing risks exposed through our relationships with suppliers, adhering to regulatory guidance, and driving operational efficiencies across risk teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The purpose of the Program Manager, Third Party Regulatory Risk is to support the development of our regulatory compliance programs and control effectiveness of the existing framework for identifying, assessing, and managing third party risks to protect Stripe.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will partner with cross-functional Risk Domain Owners, Procurement sub-teams, Legal, and other stakeholders to apply a unified Third Party Risk Framework across risk and compliance areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This person will refine our existing regulatory compliance programs across the Digital Operational Resilience Act (DORA), and other regulatory regimes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Refine existing regulatory compliance programs across the Digital Operational Resilience Act (DORA) and other regulatory regimes pertaining to third party suppliers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carry out supporting oversight activities of the regulatory compliance programs across third party suppliers (e.g., due diligence, criticality, performance monitoring, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Point of contact and subject matter expert for all internal and external audit and exam requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project management of external communications with Users, external auditors, and external regulatory examiners; including where cross functional input is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for ensuring timely resolution of identified recommendations and findings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support an oversight model for global Outsourced Service Providers as defined by global regulators (Central Bank of Ireland, etc).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular assessments of program processes to identify gaps or areas for improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in the supplier incident response framework in partnership with stakeholder incident response teams to consistently respond to incidents, track to resolution, and monitor remediation, where required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay updated on emerging trends, regulations, and industry standards related to third party risk management and integrate them into Stripe&#39;s program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in risk and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Subject matter expertise in third party risk and compliance including specific focus on US and EMEA regulations, especially DORA,&amp;nbsp; in addition to other global jurisdictions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience managing distinct projects and programs, with particularly strong skills in stakeholder management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable cleaning, organizing, analyzing, and structuring data for reporting across different audiences (e.g., Regulators, Leadership)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in leading the delivery of regulatory programs in a financial services environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of compliance and regulatory (payments) obligations including third party, outsourcing and operational resilience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in ambiguous, quickly scaling environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills—including the ability to communicate effectively with different stakeholders across the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent cross-functional collaboration skills, including navigating leadership and interpersonal working relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional organizational and time management skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to handle multiple assignments and assess and analyze data in order to solve problems, comfortably managing ambiguity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience building third party risk programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience implementing programs around regulatory frameworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Tableau or other data visualization tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Recruiting Program Management Team is dedicated to enhancing the quality and efficiency of Stripe’s Recruiting function. By executing a suite of strategic projects and programs, we optimize the caliber and productivity of our global, distinctive recruiting team. Our focus includes driving programmatic initiatives, facilitating data-informed decision-making, and steering change management to enable robust business engagement. We are looking for a talented program manager to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to building an inclusive work environment where all Stripes feel welcomed as their authentic selves—inclusive of all genders, sexual orientations, ethnicities, races, education, ages, and other personal characteristics. We work on broadening our internal diversity because we want to be culturally equipped to build products and solutions for our diverse user base.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the directly responsible individual (DRI) for one or more key centralized recruiting programs—such as Recruiter Enablement, Quality of Hire, or Business Engagement—you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and steer the program’s objectives and key result areas, including tracking and reporting metrics and overall program management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead change management initiatives within our recruiting teams and collaborate with partners to facilitate seamless transitions, tracked through change adoption metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide comprehensive enablement to all relevant stakeholders within recruiting—ensuring they are equipped with the knowledge and resources needed to excel in their roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain an updated repository of knowledge articles, ensuring all information about the program remains accurate, relevant and easily discoverable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement operational improvements across recruiting programs and processes, maximizing their effectiveness and efficiency through measurable metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design training guides and educational materials to enhance the skill set of recruiters, measured by participant feedback and performance outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Global Recruiting Leads and Hiring Managers to pinpoint and execute high-priority initiatives that elevate our recruiting efforts, with a trackable impact on hiring success rates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional initiatives by fostering impeccable communication, coordination, and execution among the recruiting team and other partners, gauged through project timelines and stakeholder satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to additional business-critical recruiting initiatives as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven expertise in program, change, and project management within a dynamic, global, high-growth environment, demonstrated through successful project outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for developing innovative programs that drive measurable quality and efficiency improvements, evidenced by previous program success metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leveraging AI tools to enhance daily operations, with specific examples of tools used and outcomes achieved&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated initiative, autonomy, and critical thinking skills with a keen attention to detail, as shown by past project performance evaluations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to think creatively and implement impactful solutions, measurable through project completion rates and effectiveness assessments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with a history of stakeholder engagement and successful presentations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive, data-driven approach to problem-solving; skilled at discerning trends and translating insights into actionable improvements, monitored through data analysis reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adaptability and a growth mindset; demonstrable flexibility in managing shifting tasks and priorities in previous roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Ability and willingness to attend to work matters outside normal business hours on an as-needed basis (this role supports a global team, so flexibility to adjust your working schedule to connect with counterparts in different time zones is preferable)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Functional experience in recruiting, with a minimum of 6 years in the field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
